org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.consed.nav

Interface NavigationElement

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNavigationElement, ConsensusNavigationElement, ReadNavigationElement

    public interface NavigationElement
    NavigationElement is an interface that represents a single record of a Consed Navigation File.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  NavigationElement.Type
      There are several different types of Navigation Element that tell consed what kind of feature this element is.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      String getComment()

      Get the id of the target to be navigated to (usually in consed this is the contig id)

    • Method Detail

      • getType

        NavigationElement.Type getType()
        Get the NavigationElement.Type of this element.
        Returns:
        the Element's type; never null.

      • getUngappedPositionRange

        Range getUngappedPositionRange()
        Get the ungapped position range of this element on the target coordinate system. For example, if this element is a NavigationElement.Type.CONSENSUS type, then this range refers to the consensus positions; if this element is a NavigationElement.Type.READ then this range refers to the read positions.
        Returns:
        the Range of this element (probably in CoordinateSystem#RESIDUE_BASED); never null.

      • getComment

        String getComment()
        Get the comment that will show up in the navigation window of consed that describes this element.
        Returns:
        a String, may be null.

      • getTargetId

        String getTargetId()
        Get the id of the target to be navigated to (usually in consed this is the contig id)
        Returns:
        the id as a String, will never be null.
